3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper compares the key size of the proposed scheme with known schemes for the same security level, which involves analyzing the computational complexity of the schemes.

5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper does not focus on software engineering, but it may involve implementation and optimization of the proposed scheme, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
